    <div class="category-intro">
      <p>A slow or unreliable home network affects everything: video calls freeze mid-sentence, 4K streams buffer at the worst moment, and smart home devices in the far corner of your house struggle to connect. The fix used to mean a single upgraded router in a central location — but modern homes with thick walls, multiple floors, and dozens of connected devices need something more capable. Mesh Wi-Fi systems have changed how home networks work, using multiple nodes placed throughout your home to create a single seamless network with consistent speeds in every room. For simpler setups, a quality router upgrade alone can dramatically improve performance and range. Wi-Fi extenders offer a budget-friendly way to push coverage further into dead zones, and powerline adapters use your home's existing electrical wiring to carry a wired-speed connection anywhere in the house. We're building out our home networking coverage with hands-on testing of mesh Wi-Fi systems, standalone routers, Wi-Fi extenders, and powerline adapters — with honest data and clear recommendations for every home size and budget.</p>
